<h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-6">Workspace Files</h1>

<p class="text-zinc-400 mb-6">
  Worktree file management is handled through plugins that hook into lifecycle events.
  Install the <strong class="text-zinc-200">Worktree Lifecycle</strong> plugin template from
  Settings &gt; Templates to get started.
</p>

<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mt-8 mb-3">Worktree lifecycle hooks</h2>
<p class="text-zinc-400 mb-4">
  Plugins can observe two worktree events:
</p>
<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-zinc-400 space-y-1 mb-6">
  <li><code class="text-zinc-300 bg-zinc-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">worktree_created</code> &mdash;
    fires after a new worktree is set up (copy files, install dependencies)</li>
  <li><code class="text-zinc-300 bg-zinc-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">worktree_deleted</code> &mdash;
    fires when a worktree is removed (cleanup, deregister)</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mt-8 mb-3">Example: copy files into worktrees</h2>
<pre class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300 font-mono overflow-x-auto mb-6"><code>-- plugins/worktree-lifecycle/init.lua
local hooks = require("hub.hooks")

hooks.on("worktree_created", "my-copy", function(ctx)
    local repo = ctx.repo or worktree.repo_root()
    local src = repo .. "/.env"
    if fs.exists(src) then
        fs.copy(src, ctx.path .. "/.env")
    end
end)</code></pre>

<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mt-8 mb-3">Example: manage Claude trust</h2>
<pre class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300 font-mono overflow-x-auto mb-6"><code>-- Auto-trust worktree on create
hooks.on("worktree_created", "claude-trust", function(ctx)
    json.file_set("~/.claude.json",
        "projects." .. ctx.path .. ".hasTrustDialogAccepted", true)
end)

-- Clean up trust entry on delete
hooks.on("worktree_deleted", "claude-cleanup", function(ctx)
    json.file_delete("~/.claude.json", "projects." .. ctx.path)
end)</code></pre>
